    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "How are you causing network breakage? Default linux TCP timeout can be as large as 15-20mins. Client side socket won't fail until TCP timeout happens. For faster connection breakage detection, you should enable keepalive on the channel. In your case, since server is detecting the breakage and stopping the stream, client will have to restart the RPC after it also detects connection breakage."
