    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If the network breakage is such that only TCP timeout can detect it then server will take that long to call onError() of the responseObserver. You can use keepalive on the server side too in order to detect network breakage early. I will close this issue since there does not seem to be a bug here. You seem to be using grpc-java so if you think there is a bug please open an issue in [java repo](https://github.com/grpc/grpc-java/) with a minimal repro.  "
